                <h2>The Androgen Receptor: Why the Hormone Fails</h2>

                <p>Here is the most devastating reality: You can have the highest levels of Testosterone and DHT on planet earth, yet still have completely bald cheeks. Why?</p>
                <p>The hormone circulating in your blood must have a place to "land." Your hair follicle has <strong>Androgen Receptors</strong>, which act as biological catchers mitts. If your DNA simply did not build enough androgen receptors on your cheek follicles, the massive amounts of DHT rushing past in the blood cannot be "caught" or absorbed. The hormone floats uselessly straight past the target.</p>
                <p>If you lack receptors, no amount of physical exercise or <a href="does-minoxidil-work-for-beard.php">topical solutions</a> will grow the hair naturally. This severe genetic block is exactly what <a href="what-is-patchy-beard.php">causes impossible patches</a> on otherwise extremely fit, healthy men.</p>

